page.title: 03ECOLOGY , FISH
page.content: The Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food found sole and plaice nursery grounds in the middle and outer Humber. The main fish to be found in the estuary are :- Bass, Brill, Bullhead, Coley, Cod, Eel, Herring, Mackerel, Bib, Salmon, Thornback Ray, Turbot, Weever and Whiting. Other fish to be found in the estuary include Dab, Skipper, Butterfish, Plaice, Sole and Haddock. The area at the Southern end of the block is the North boundary of an area recognised by the Nature Conservancy Council as a site of Special Scientific Interest.
